<h2>Some Notes on Spelling</h2>

<p>Mohs Hardness Scale is named after its inventor, Friedrich Mohs.  This m=
eans that an apostrophe is not needed when typing the name of the test. "Mo=
h's" and "Mohs' " are incorrect.</p>

<p>Google is really smart about these names.  You can even type "Moe's Hard=
ness Scale" as a query and Google knows to return results for "Mohs Hardnes=
s Scale."   &nbsp;  :-)</p>
</section>


